	<Title>
		Is your hearing at risk?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Repeated exposure to loud noise can damage the delicate, sound-sensitive hair cells in your inner ear. You can&apos;t reverse hearing loss, so take steps to protect your hearing: 1. Turn down the volume on headphones. 2. Wear earplugs or other protection when you&apos;re around noisy tools, equipment or firearms. 3. If you&apos;re frequently around loud noise, ask your doctor about yearly hearing exams.&lt;/p&gt;
